text: Love like the sand fading in hand
I can't deny I should be frank. But when you leave, teardrops can not end.
Your beloved tea, your perfume brand. We have grown apart, all things in vain.
Forget me not, why do you live in this land. How can I face this pain, I can not stand.
How can I heal, heal my broken heart without love. Even breathe is hard, when you go so far.
But how could we break up? Our love's like the shooting star. Cease your love, lost my heart.
